Class LandUnit

java.lang.Object
  sluce2.landscape.component.LandUnit
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:

public abstract class LandUnit
extends java.lang.Object
implements Landcover, EcosystemModel

A LandUnit is a generic object used to track the proportion of land-cover types (e.g. tree cover, impervious, grass) within the boundary of the particular land-unit object.

LandUnits act as a container for geographic and biophysical location-based state variables as well as the natural processes that it may undergo. Each LandUnit is an independent automation in the model.

Meghan Hutchins
